1
00:00:14,890 --> 00:00:17,240
Dream.

2
00:00:17,730 --> 00:00:21,150
I wish I could dream of you...

3
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,710
I don’t think I can sing.

4
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:28,420
Try a little more, Mai.

5
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:30,730
Just a bit more.

6
00:00:31,190 --> 00:00:33,190
I know my little brother can do it.

7
00:00:34,350 --> 00:00:36,170
Are you saying I’m not trying hard enough?

8
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:37,000
No.

9
00:00:37,540 --> 00:00:39,130
That’s not what I meant.

10
00:00:40,260 --> 00:00:42,430
I believe you can do it

11
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:44,020
if you put in more effort.

12
00:00:44,430 --> 00:00:45,850
So I’m not putting in enough effort?

13
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:47,420
No, that’s not it.

14
00:00:47,420 --> 00:00:48,190
Forget it.

15
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:49,650
I’m done.

16
00:00:50,530 --> 00:00:51,790
I’m not debuting.

17
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,190
I guess this is as far as my dream goes.

18
00:00:56,330 --> 00:00:57,950
You should open your own music label

19
00:00:57,950 --> 00:01:00,100
and debut some artists.

20
00:01:01,810 --> 00:01:02,870
Don’t waste your time on me.

21
00:01:21,910 --> 00:01:23,870
Sorry, I wasn’t looking.

22
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:24,910
I’m really sorry.

23
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:26,360
It’s okay.

24
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,490
I wasn’t paying attention.

25
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,150
Well,

26
00:01:29,670 --> 00:01:32,170
are you auditioning for Ultimate Wolf too?

27
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:33,580
Mhm.

28
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:43,270
Hello, bro.

29
00:01:46,789 --> 00:01:48,229
Alright, I’ll help you.

30
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,480
He looks familiar.

31
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:04,390
It’s like we’ve met before.

32
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:07,790
He’s quite good looking.

33
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,990
If he joined our group,

34
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:12,400
he’d be the visual.

35
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,900
More like the vicious.

36
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:17,270
He annoys me.

37
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:19,760
Hey, Yu.

38
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:22,060
You said the car was almost here.

39
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:23,020
Where is it?

40
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,790
It’s almost here.

41
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,700
There it is.

42
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:31,260
It’s here.

43
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,180
Come this way.

44
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,060
A rescue vehicle?

45
00:03:35,579 --> 00:03:36,340
Yeah.

46
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:38,760
Cutter is in bad shape,

47
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,800
so I called them.

48
00:03:43,780 --> 00:03:46,280
No one will want to be in our group anymore.

49
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:48,650
Isn’t it pretty unique?

50
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,500
Maybe we can appear on The Ghost show.

51
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,540
Let’s go.

52
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:05,980
Not a contract.

53
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:08,790
I had Sean prepare mascot costumes.

54
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:09,980
Four of them.

55
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,840
You’ll perform on Children’s Day

56
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,580
at Wat Yai Nong Khai School.

57
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:17,829
Hm.

58
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:18,910
Whoa.

59
00:04:19,149 --> 00:04:19,959
Damn.

60
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,040
Hm.

61
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:25,050
Not a contract.

62
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:26,590
Hey, bro.

63
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:28,490
What happened last night?

64
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:32,570
Why did I dream about doing yoga?

65
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,730
What yoga? Bruh.

66
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,340
You were so wasted,

67
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:37,880
but Yu took care of you.

68
00:04:38,180 --> 00:04:40,230
Otherwise, you would’ve been a mess.

69
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:42,830
Cantaloupe, my baby.

70
00:04:42,830 --> 00:04:44,820
Don’t talk to him. He hasn’t showered.

71
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:45,740
He smells terrible.

72
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,890
Damn, you're right.

73
00:04:51,330 --> 00:04:53,760
Take some, Cutter. It’ll help with your hangover.

74
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,300
Whoa, thank you.

75
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,480
You know me so well.

76
00:04:58,930 --> 00:05:00,040
Ow!

77
00:05:00,450 --> 00:05:03,160
Ah! Ahh! It’s hot!

78
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:05,530
Why didn’t you warn me?

79
00:05:05,890 --> 00:05:09,600
If I burn my tongue, how am I gonna rap?

80
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,740
And it’s mala flavor. My tongue is getting numb.

81
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:14,670
Hey, guys.

82
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:16,680
I’m wondering.

83
00:05:17,470 --> 00:05:20,970
Is Boss really making us wear mascot costumes?

84
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:25,270
If we really have to wear it, can I be the purple one?

85
00:05:25,530 --> 00:05:28,120
That one looks pretty and expensive.

86
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:29,910
Haha.

87
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:31,310
The purple one?

88
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,430
Don’t be kidding.

89
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:34,390
You’re going to be the yellow one.

90
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:37,270
With all that flashy and cheerful energy.

91
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:39,640
Then what color am I?

92
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:46,140
Yu.

93
00:05:46,140 --> 00:05:47,340
You’re the red one.

94
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:49,590
Because you’re cute.

95
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,720
Not a contract.

96
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:57,320
I had Sean prepare mascot costumes.

97
00:05:57,770 --> 00:05:59,150
You’ll perform on Children’s Day

98
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,920
at Wat Yai Nong Khai School.

99
00:06:01,030 --> 00:06:01,910
Guys.

100
00:06:01,910 --> 00:06:02,470
Huh?

101
00:06:03,170 --> 00:06:04,230
I’m going to talk to Boss.

102
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,340
I’m quitting.

103
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,000
What?

104
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,460
Calm down, bro.

105
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,340
You can’t quit yet.

106
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:17,700
Wait until we shower first.

107
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:20,510
Then we’ll quit together, okay?

108
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,580
You look happy.

109
00:06:34,730 --> 00:06:36,260
Because I’m so happy.

110
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:54,550
Boss.

111
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:56,210
What is it, Jeng?

112
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:57,290
I…

113
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,520
We want to quit.

114
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,120
Huh?

115
00:07:00,410 --> 00:07:01,170
What did you say?

116
00:07:02,530 --> 00:07:04,700
See? I told you we should practice first.

117
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:08,160
Well, I thought Boss would say,

118
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:11,480
“Hah. Good riddance.”

119
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,910
Something like that.

120
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:13,830
What the heck?

121
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:20,100
I’ve tried my best, Boss.

122
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:23,060
Maybe being an idol

123
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:25,210
really isn’t for me.

124
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:27,510
I did everything I could,

125
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:31,730
but the result was the opposite.

126
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:35,590
Thank you for giving me opportunities

127
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:38,010
and for trusting me.

128
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:41,390
Even though my last boy group failed,

129
00:07:41,659 --> 00:07:43,620
you still let me create a new one.

130
00:07:44,780 --> 00:07:48,280
Now I admit it.

131
00:07:49,330 --> 00:07:50,610
I’m just a loser.

132
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:53,710
I don’t want to waste more of your time.

133
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:57,860
Let’s disband the group.

134
00:08:08,790 --> 00:08:10,020
Who said this isn’t for you?

135
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:16,680
And I’m not disbanding the group.

136
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,350
But Boss...

137
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:22,030
Jeng doesn’t want to be a mascot

138
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:25,220
He wants to be an idol.

139
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:27,280
And he was born to be one, Boss.

140
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,900
I’m not making you wear a mascot.

141
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,679
We will...

142
00:08:35,010 --> 00:08:36,169
debut a new boy group.

143
00:08:36,169 --> 00:08:37,049
Huh?

144
00:08:37,049 --> 00:08:37,980
Really, Boss?

145
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:38,830
Yes.

146
00:08:38,830 --> 00:08:42,419
But four members are too few.

147
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:44,500
It doesn’t feel complete yet.

148
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:46,410
We need another member.

149
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:49,290
Sure, I’ll help you find him.

150
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:51,180
I’ll listen to the fortune teller

151
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,870
and go to every place we missed.

152
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:53,810
Yes, yes!

153
00:08:53,810 --> 00:08:55,440
Whether it’s north, south,

154
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,890
or sailing across the ocean,

155
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:58,550
I’ll find him for you.

156
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:02,170
Me too, I’ll look at dance cover schools.

157
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:03,310
That’s right.

158
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:05,650
I’ll search at crime scenes too.

159
00:09:05,650 --> 00:09:06,790
Places where someone just—

160
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:08,590
Shh.

161
00:09:08,950 --> 00:09:09,930
Enough.

162
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,730
I already found a new member.

163
00:09:13,810 --> 00:09:16,130
Sean, open the door.

164
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:17,870
Let’s welcome our new member.

165
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:18,630
Yes, sir.

166
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:37,340
This is Mai, our new member.

167
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:38,810
From now on,

168
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:42,190
Mai will become a member of your group, Ahh wolf.

169
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:45,270
Take some responsibility for throwing up at it.

170
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,110
We meet again.

171
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:52,400
But we don’t know each other yet, Boss.

172
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,560
We don’t know if our positions will overlap.

173
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:56,150
And we don’t know what he’s like.

174
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:58,520
At least someone has to accept it first.

175
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,330
Do you have a better option?

176
00:10:00,330 --> 00:10:02,040
We don’t have time to choose anymore.

177
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:05,140
Or do you want me to...

178
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:06,720
Ah!

179
00:10:09,180 --> 00:10:12,830
Boss really has a great vision.

180
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,890
I wonder if our group will become famous

181
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:19,640
for being talented or being pretty.

182
00:10:22,340 --> 00:10:24,410
Hello, my new friend.

183
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,750
My name is Cutter.

184
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:29,140
Nice to meet you.

185
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:32,870
Hi, I’m Fong. Welcome.

186
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:35,350
I’m the main dancer who can dance any style.

187
00:10:35,350 --> 00:10:37,500
But I’m good at Korean songs.

188
00:10:37,810 --> 00:10:39,030
Let me know if you need anything.

189
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:42,580
And what’s your name?

190
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:46,970
His name is Yu.

191
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:48,310
He’s not a talkative person,

192
00:10:48,310 --> 00:10:50,500
so if you want to talk to him, just talk to me.

193
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,510
I’m better at talking.

194
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:52,950
And this is…

195
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:56,620
the first member of our group, Jeng.

196
00:10:57,070 --> 00:10:59,110
You’ll get close soon.

197
00:10:59,110 --> 00:11:02,260
He’s just a little sensitive today.

198
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:06,190
I guarantee that when we perform next time,

199
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,640
we’re going to be a hit, no doubt!

200
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:12,520
You’re Jeng?

201
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:19,080
Alright, everyone.

202
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,680
Do your best.

203
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,520
Jeng, hurry up and write a new song.

204
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:28,470
Our label has to become more famous than Bai Liu’s.

205
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:29,790
But Boss…

206
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:31,600
No buts.

207
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:35,200
Now we have a new member, let’s go practice dancing.

208
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,230
After that, shall we go celebrate?

209
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:38,540
Sounds good.

210
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:39,830
Let’s go practice dancing.

211
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:41,270
Let’s go, my friend.

212
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,590
He looks familiar, though.

213
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,270
This time,

214
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:56,030
you’ll see what I’m made of, Bai Liu!

215
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,780
What are you looking at?

216
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:00,910
The future.

217
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:03,300
Why are you still here?

218
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:06,440
Take them to the Wolf Den practice room.

219
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:07,820
Yes, sir.

220
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,510
Bai Liu.

221
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,500
You’ll see!

222
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:31,080
This is the Wolf Den practice room.

223
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:38,450
Is this really our practice room?

224
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:42,660
It’s covered in dust.

225
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:46,050
Can we really practice here?

226
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:52,530
Come on in.

227
00:12:59,370 --> 00:13:00,400
Whoa.

228
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:02,550
It's pretty big.

229
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,340
Is it still good?

230
00:13:11,420 --> 00:13:14,130
This is the legendary secret room of our label.

231
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:18,050
Our first trainee used to practice here

232
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,550
before going to Korea to debut.

233
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,580
Korea?

234
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:24,360
Our label had someone go to Korea?

235
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:27,100
Yes, that trainee…

236
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,980
practiced every day before flying to Korea when he was nine.

237
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:32,550
He was determined to become an artist.

238
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,240
But in the end,

239
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,530
he lost to someone with connections in Korea.

240
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:40,400
That’s so sad.

241
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:43,220
Where is he now?

242
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,460
Oh.

243
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,100
He is—

244
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,380
Ahem!

245
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,550
Shall we start practicing?

246
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:53,080
This is why you’re not making any progress.

247
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:55,720
Yeah, let’s practice.

248
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,760
Come on.

249
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:59,380
Let’s practice, guys

250
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,280
Can we practice here?

251
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:01,560
It'll do.

252
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:03,780
I’ll turn on the music.

253
00:14:32,050 --> 00:14:33,930
I’m so exhausted.

254
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,370
Freaking exhausted!

255
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:36,550
Bruh.

256
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:40,820
What are you tired of?

257
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:43,660
You moved like an old man.

258
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:44,940
No way.

259
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:46,330
You barely danced.

260
00:14:46,330 --> 00:14:49,260
-That’s you.
-No, you.

261
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:50,690
Alright, stop fighting.

262
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:53,160
Ha.

263
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:56,130
Even though we’re tired, we’re happy.

264
00:14:56,130 --> 00:14:57,890
Because we have a new member.

265
00:14:58,060 --> 00:14:59,850
Everything feels right since you joined us.

266
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:00,760
Honestly,

267
00:15:01,590 --> 00:15:04,730
I’ve never seen anyone as handsome as him.

268
00:15:04,930 --> 00:15:05,600
Oh.

269
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,550
I’m curious.

270
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:10,630
The name "Ahh wolf" of our group.

271
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,210
It's dog howling, right?

272
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:15,780
Is it considered lucky?

273
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,130
I don’t know.

274
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,150
It just feels kinda weird.

275
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,110
What do you think?

276
00:15:20,110 --> 00:15:21,780
Well, if our label is a wolf,

277
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:24,390
then we’re the howls of love.

278
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:26,180
Whoa!

279
00:15:26,570 --> 00:15:27,550
Damn.

280
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:30,650
You nailed it. That line really hits hard.

281
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:32,300
It's like an ads tagline.

282
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,460
Wait,

283
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:34,850
how did you know?

284
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,980
Yeah, how?

285
00:15:38,650 --> 00:15:40,330
I asked when I signed the contract.

286
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:43,610
-Oh, that time.
-He was so careful.

287
00:15:44,060 --> 00:15:45,760
Don’t tell me

288
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:47,610
you signed without reading it.

289
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:49,240
You didn’t ask any questions?

290
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:49,990
Oh.

291
00:15:50,370 --> 00:15:52,610
A little bit.

292
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:55,500
Boss wouldn’t scam us anyway.

293
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:57,880
He's Si Tian Sinwatchara.

294
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:00,990
Scam or not,

295
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:02,930
shouldn’t you be careful?

296
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:04,800
At least,

297
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,320
you should protect yourself.

298
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:11,310
What if the contract said

299
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,590
you have to pay 10 million if your group fail.

300
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:15,390
What will you do?

301
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,010
You can’t even figure this out?

302
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:20,710
Someone like you

303
00:16:21,220 --> 00:16:23,750
surely don't know what friendship is.

304
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,500
Wait, wait.

305
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:27,920
Calm down, guys.

306
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:31,210
I read it, and there’s nothing like that.

307
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:33,570
It only talks about income and profit sharing.

308
00:16:33,570 --> 00:16:35,470
But right now, we don’t have to worry.

309
00:16:35,470 --> 00:16:36,210
Do you know why?

310
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:36,820
Why?

311
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,550
We haven’t made any money.

312
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,940
So we don’t have to worry.

313
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:42,460
Yeah.

314
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:44,070
When is the train coming?

315
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:44,910
Right?

316
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:48,400
At least the MRT has air conditioning.

317
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:48,950
Yeah.

318
00:16:51,350 --> 00:16:52,350
I'm so tired.

319
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:55,210
I wanna eat. I wanna eat!

320
00:16:55,210 --> 00:16:57,680
You can take my jacket if you're cold.

321
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:59,270
Hey, the train is here.

322
00:16:59,270 --> 00:16:59,900
Uh…

323
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,180
It’s here.

324
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:02,710
Come on.

325
00:17:02,710 --> 00:17:03,620
Wait.

326
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:07,020
Let the people inside get off first.

327
00:17:07,980 --> 00:17:08,760
Right.

328
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:09,930
I'm so hungry.

329
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:12,380
Let’s go.

330
00:17:15,829 --> 00:17:16,500
Ugh.

331
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:19,060
I don’t understand Boss at all.

332
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:22,280
Our company has practice rooms.

333
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:25,700
Why did we have to come this far?

334
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:29,940
Good thing we have the MRT here,

335
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:32,950
so it doesn't feel too far.

336
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:37,000
Do you know the word “laying low”?

337
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,510
It’s when we take things seriously, and hide our failures.

338
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,670
We lay low.

339
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,140
But it’s okay.

340
00:17:43,540 --> 00:17:46,500
Think of it as a training strategy before we come back shining

341
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,300
with style and skill.

342
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,290
I agree.

343
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:51,680
Boss wants us to be wolves.

344
00:17:52,150 --> 00:17:53,430
But now,

345
00:17:54,350 --> 00:17:55,400
we’re just underdogs.

346
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:58,450
I think he wants us to work hard

347
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:00,520
and bring back greatness.

348
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:02,860
No matter where one practices,

349
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:06,470
if you have no talent, you’re just a stray dog.

350
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:09,990
Hey, hey.

351
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:14,860
Let’s not worry about practicing yet.

352
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:17,320
I think we should

353
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:20,080
talk about our positions first.

354
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:22,510
For example, I’m the main rapper.

355
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,730
What’s up, bro? You know?

356
00:18:24,730 --> 00:18:26,550
Hey, I want to be…

357
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,060
the main dancer. Please give it to me

358
00:18:29,390 --> 00:18:30,460
Go ahead.

359
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:31,840
I’ll be the main vocalist.

360
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:34,860
Well.

361
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,130
My position is…

362
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:41,150
I signed the contract as the group’s center.

363
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:41,860
Huh?

364
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,870
Damn!

365
00:18:44,860 --> 00:18:46,390
You’re the center?

366
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,120
Mhm.

367
00:18:47,650 --> 00:18:48,390
Wait a second.

368
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:49,690
If you're the center...

369
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:52,390
Aren't you taking Jeng’s spot?

370
00:18:53,490 --> 00:18:54,250
No.

371
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,430
I can be in any position.

372
00:18:56,430 --> 00:18:58,130
As long as it benefits our group.

373
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,450
You should be the center.

374
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:07,090
How about this.

375
00:19:07,090 --> 00:19:10,550
Someone handsome and charming like you

376
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:11,790
should be the visual.

377
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:14,220
You have a handsome face, a great figure,

378
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:19,060
and your talent is unmatched.

379
00:19:19,850 --> 00:19:22,110
This position is just for you.

380
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:23,770
I agree.

381
00:19:24,220 --> 00:19:24,950
I’m getting shy.

382
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:29,630
P’Sean.

383
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:33,860
Are we going to eat omakase tonight?

384
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,570
The boss said we need to cut costs.

385
00:19:38,570 --> 00:19:39,510
Cut costs?

386
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:42,440
We can only afford noodles.

387
00:19:42,450 --> 00:19:43,830
Noodles?

388
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,750
Noodles.

389
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,960
Noodles? Noodles again?

390
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:50,730
My hands are becoming noddles.

391
00:20:02,820 --> 00:20:03,710
It’s really good.

392
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,000
It's so nice.

393
00:20:07,590 --> 00:20:09,670
Should we ask for more bitter melon?

394
00:20:09,670 --> 00:20:10,590
Yeah, get some.

395
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:12,810
Auntie, can I have more bitter melon, please?

396
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,190
Call me big sis.

397
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:19,420
Normal people don’t like bitter melons, you know.

398
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,710
You’re so cute!

399
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:23,810
Eat up.

400
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,760
Enjoy your meal.

401
00:20:26,940 --> 00:20:27,720
Want some more?

402
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:30,550
Big sis?

403
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,600
Jeng.

404
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:37,900
Don’t we have a songwriter?

405
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,530
P’Amp, P’Golf F.HERO,

406
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:42,160
P’Tan from Lipta,

407
00:20:42,810 --> 00:20:44,420
or P’Mix Chalermsri.

408
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:45,890
Don’t we have anyone like that?

409
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:48,300
It’d be nice if we had money to hire someone.

410
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:49,960
It probably costs a fortune.

411
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:54,200
So who usually writes the songs?

412
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:56,350
We all help.

413
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,140
But I wrote most of them.

414
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:01,810
You’re so good.

415
00:21:05,460 --> 00:21:06,200
Yu.

416
00:21:06,940 --> 00:21:10,810
Why does your noodles look so bland?

417
00:21:11,410 --> 00:21:12,710
I don’t like bitter melon.

418
00:21:13,220 --> 00:21:14,150
It’s bitter.

419
00:21:16,190 --> 00:21:17,930
Why don’t you try it?

420
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:21,330
Who knows, one day

421
00:21:22,010 --> 00:21:23,240
you might fall in love with it.

422
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:25,340
Should I?

423
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,020
Here.

424
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,090
Try a bite.

425
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:33,080
Say ah.

426
00:21:35,780 --> 00:21:36,510
How is it?

427
00:21:39,580 --> 00:21:40,450
Bitter melon.

428
00:21:41,830 --> 00:21:42,570
Be my love.

429
00:21:43,770 --> 00:21:44,460
Oh.

430
00:21:44,730 --> 00:21:46,120
Bitter melon, be my love.

431
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:48,920
There are songs about sharks and mangosteens.

432
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:51,290
Now it's time for bitter melons.

433
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,060
Ahh Wolf!

434
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:54,340
Oh.

435
00:21:54,830 --> 00:21:56,730
Bitter melon, be my love.

436
00:21:57,220 --> 00:21:59,440
That sounds catchy.

437
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,080
Right?

438
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:02,480
If we make a good melody and lyrics,

439
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:04,370
it’ll be a hit.

440
00:22:05,270 --> 00:22:05,980
Who knows,

441
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:09,670
this might be our lucky bitter melon.

442
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,560
I’ve found my passion.

443
00:22:14,380 --> 00:22:16,390
Do you want a bitter melon?

444
00:22:21,620 --> 00:22:23,050
Hello, I’m here.

445
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:26,170
Huh? You’re already there?

446
00:22:26,990 --> 00:22:28,150
I just woke up.

447
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:29,000
What?

448
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:31,530
I’ll be there soon.

449
00:22:32,170 --> 00:22:34,350
It’s fine. Don’t rush.

450
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:36,430
I have Jeng.

451
00:22:39,070 --> 00:22:40,900
Okay, see you.

452
00:22:50,850 --> 00:22:51,520
Hey.

453
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:53,750
What about the others?

454
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,450
-The others?
-Yeah.

455
00:22:59,450 --> 00:23:01,100
They’ll come soon.

456
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:02,900
So, how’s the song writing?

457
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:06,250
It’s not going anywhere.

458
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:07,940
I can’t think of any lyrics.

459
00:23:09,550 --> 00:23:10,810
Doesn’t something like this

460
00:23:11,780 --> 00:23:13,730
come from your love experience?

461
00:23:15,530 --> 00:23:16,670
Love?

462
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:19,580
I don’t have any love experience.

463
00:23:20,060 --> 00:23:21,230
I only hang out with Boss.

464
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:24,010
Just try it. Maybe it’ll help you.

465
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:30,880
Well.

466
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:33,430
Easy for you to say.

467
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:35,620
A guy like you…

468
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,050
must be an expert in love.

469
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:39,620
No.

470
00:23:40,450 --> 00:23:41,760
I’ve never been in a relationship.

471
00:23:42,310 --> 00:23:43,120
Really?

472
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:44,800
Are you serious?

473
00:23:45,540 --> 00:23:46,310
Yeah.

474
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:48,840
I used to focus only on studying.

475
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:51,110
I was always the class president.

476
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:52,720
I’ve never had a lover.

477
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:58,030
Then…

478
00:23:58,510 --> 00:24:01,710
Will a class president give in to a group leader?

479
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:06,930
I’d only give in to one person.

480
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:17,450
So...

481
00:24:18,090 --> 00:24:19,980
I’m going to help Boss find some clothes.

482
00:24:20,550 --> 00:24:21,730
Do you want to come with me?

483
00:24:22,540 --> 00:24:23,330
Sure.

484
00:24:23,830 --> 00:24:24,760
My leader.

485
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:35,770
If you agree to go,

486
00:24:36,900 --> 00:24:38,170
make a pufferfish face first.

487
00:24:39,930 --> 00:24:40,900
A pufferfish face?

488
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:41,470
Yeah.

489
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:43,410
How?

490
00:24:43,740 --> 00:24:44,540
Like this.

491
00:24:52,190 --> 00:24:52,990
Puff up more.

492
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:55,970
Even more.

493
00:24:59,810 --> 00:25:00,590
More.

494
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:04,050
Alright, that’s enough.

495
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:06,060
Come here.

496
00:25:06,470 --> 00:25:09,290
Let me see the lyrics.

497
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:18,800
Seriously,

498
00:25:19,340 --> 00:25:20,540
these clothes are cool.

499
00:25:21,370 --> 00:25:22,780
It looks pretty sporty.

500
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:24,270
Hmm.

501
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,880
Boss said our next concept look

502
00:25:28,140 --> 00:25:29,690
is sporty vibe.

503
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,420
But I don’t know how to style it.

504
00:25:36,450 --> 00:25:36,950
Here.

505
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,340
Try this one.

506
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:46,080
I’ve never worn this style before.

507
00:25:46,610 --> 00:25:48,290
I usually just dress the same way.

508
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:51,880
It’d be nice if our agency had a stylist.

509
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,740
Try this style then.

510
00:25:55,690 --> 00:25:56,990
I’ll be your stylist.

511
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:02,680
I’ll pick out your whole look.

512
00:26:04,580 --> 00:26:05,540
But you…

513
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:09,970
have to wear what I choose for you,

514
00:26:14,190 --> 00:26:15,790
and step into my world.

515
00:26:24,340 --> 00:26:25,450
You too.

516
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,440
Wear what I choose,

517
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:29,660
and step into my world as well.

518
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:33,880
Let’s try it on.

519
00:26:34,390 --> 00:26:36,280
Yes, leader.

520
00:26:45,140 --> 00:26:46,270
Hello.

521
00:26:48,870 --> 00:26:50,010
Are you here to see me?

522
00:26:50,010 --> 00:26:50,670
Master.

523
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:52,030
Looks like

524
00:26:52,470 --> 00:26:55,030
their agency always has projects with fans.

525
00:26:55,730 --> 00:26:57,080
Who’s that?

526
00:26:58,430 --> 00:27:00,790
He’s an actor

527
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:02,890
from “The Crisis”, sir.

528
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:05,100
Bai Liu hired him to make a song.

529
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,440
By the way,

530
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:12,700
do we have to dress up this much?

531
00:27:13,770 --> 00:27:15,700
We can’t let Bai Liu know we’re here.

532
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:16,940
It’s embarrassing.

533
00:27:18,670 --> 00:27:21,180
But we dressed like Power Rangers.

534
00:27:21,490 --> 00:27:22,350
Doesn’t this

535
00:27:22,950 --> 00:27:24,470
make us stand out even more?

536
00:27:24,470 --> 00:27:25,490
Come on.

537
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:27,880
Little deer.

538
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:31,170
Just by walking in,

539
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:33,090
You gave yourself away.

540
00:27:34,130 --> 00:27:35,380
You raise a deer?

541
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:47,360
Jarassi.

542
00:27:48,020 --> 00:27:50,420
Do we have a kid project today?

543
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:54,230
I don’t think so.

544
00:27:54,230 --> 00:27:56,020
I haven’t heard anything about it.

545
00:27:57,640 --> 00:28:01,540
Look at those Power Rangers over there.

546
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:04,950
Is it one of our CSR projects?

547
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,290
Shall we go take a look?

548
00:28:07,730 --> 00:28:08,540
Let's go.

549
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:16,510
What are you doing at my agency?

550
00:28:17,340 --> 00:28:20,690
Which project are you working on?

551
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:24,310
Remember not to go upstairs today.

552
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:28,510
They’re rehearsing for Lisa’s year end concert.

553
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:32,120
You don’t want to talk?

554
00:28:32,530 --> 00:28:34,400
If you don’t talk to me,

555
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:37,690
I’ll let you talk to Nong Ngor Ngae.

556
00:28:37,690 --> 00:28:38,390
Huh?

557
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:41,480
We’ll talk.

558
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,340
Could you help us buy these?

559
00:28:45,340 --> 00:28:48,840
The proceeds wil go to the children.

560
00:28:49,020 --> 00:28:50,320
Yes, please.

561
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,200
How cute.

562
00:28:53,750 --> 00:28:55,760
Helping the kids.

563
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:56,890
Would you like to buy some?

564
00:28:57,170 --> 00:28:59,940
Sure. I’ll help you,

565
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:03,660
so your school won’t have to close down.

566
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:08,120
How much is all this?

567
00:29:09,150 --> 00:29:10,580
Is 1,000 baht enough?

568
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:13,720
Yes, it is.

569
00:29:14,540 --> 00:29:17,890
Would you like to pay by transfer or cash?

570
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:18,770
Uh.

571
00:29:18,770 --> 00:29:21,510
This is suspicious.

572
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:23,380
Why do you want us to transfer money?

573
00:29:23,380 --> 00:29:26,750
These days, there are many scammers

574
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:29,750
who trick people into transferring money like this.

575
00:29:29,750 --> 00:29:32,480
I better call security.

576
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:34,930
Wait, please wait.

577
00:29:35,910 --> 00:29:38,120
Here you go.

578
00:29:38,420 --> 00:29:39,600
You’re not selling anymore?

579
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:40,660
Uh…

580
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:42,480
Please don’t forget to help our school.

581
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:44,290
Please.

582
00:29:44,630 --> 00:29:45,640
Let’s go.

583
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:46,630
Thank you.

584
00:29:48,250 --> 00:29:50,440
Young Master, I think…

585
00:29:50,990 --> 00:29:53,000
they’re really suspicious.

586
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,380
We should call security.

587
00:29:55,950 --> 00:29:58,770
No need. I know who they are.

588
00:29:59,030 --> 00:30:00,710
What are they playing at?

589
00:30:01,910 --> 00:30:03,420
Hello, Bai Liu.

590
00:30:03,700 --> 00:30:06,740
Why are those Power Rangers running around like that?

591
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:09,630
They almost knocked over our agency sign.

592
00:30:09,630 --> 00:30:10,480
Really?

593
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:12,670
Are they here to sell something?

594
00:30:13,490 --> 00:30:15,510
But they came in a BMW.

595
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:16,630
Oh?

596
00:30:16,630 --> 00:30:17,950
Their sales must be good.

597
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:19,370
You can join them.

598
00:30:19,370 --> 00:30:21,330
But you don’t need a mascot costume,

599
00:30:21,580 --> 00:30:24,610
because you already look like one.

600
00:30:24,610 --> 00:30:27,110
For god’s sake, look at yourself first.

601
00:30:27,110 --> 00:30:27,820
Why?

602
00:30:27,820 --> 00:30:31,240
If I’m a mascot, you’re a pregnant male seahorse!

603
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:32,140
So what?

604
00:30:32,140 --> 00:30:33,060
You little brat.

605
00:30:33,060 --> 00:30:35,270
You’ve got some nerve.

606
00:30:37,350 --> 00:30:39,390
Come on, stop fighting.

607
00:30:39,390 --> 00:30:40,760
You take one each.

608
00:30:41,390 --> 00:30:43,720
I think…

609
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:45,870
I have a job for you guys.

610
00:30:50,380 --> 00:30:52,950
We’re so late. Will Jeng get mad?

611
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:55,050
We’re only a little late.

612
00:30:55,050 --> 00:30:56,920
Jeng is nice. He won’t be mad.

613
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:58,270
It’s been an hour, though.

614
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:01,520
Come to think of it,

615
00:31:02,150 --> 00:31:03,900
this place has a good atmosphere.

616
00:31:04,730 --> 00:31:06,170
It’s peaceful,

617
00:31:07,420 --> 00:31:08,730
and has lots of trees.

618
00:31:09,320 --> 00:31:11,880
No wonder Jeng likes to write songs here.

619
00:31:13,850 --> 00:31:14,530
Uh…

620
00:31:15,790 --> 00:31:18,970
Cutter, can I ask you something?

621
00:31:19,550 --> 00:31:20,750
What is it?

622
00:31:22,260 --> 00:31:23,620
Do you like me, Cutter?

623
00:31:33,870 --> 00:31:34,800
Why...

624
00:31:36,860 --> 00:31:38,240
Why do you think that?

625
00:31:38,780 --> 00:31:39,430
Well…

626
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:41,950
There were many times

627
00:31:43,150 --> 00:31:44,830
when you seemed worried about me.

628
00:31:46,210 --> 00:31:50,200
And I could tell from your eyes.

629
00:31:52,430 --> 00:31:55,150
Yu, why are you so cute?

630
00:31:56,190 --> 00:31:57,460
Cutter, you're drunk.

631
00:32:13,030 --> 00:32:14,820
Why don’t you try it?

632
00:32:14,820 --> 00:32:16,870
Who knows, one day

633
00:32:16,870 --> 00:32:20,070
you might fall in love with it.

634
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:25,170
You like me, don’t you?

635
00:32:36,060 --> 00:32:36,830
If…

636
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:39,930
I told you

637
00:32:41,260 --> 00:32:42,490
that I liked you,

638
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:44,410
what would you do?

639
00:32:45,650 --> 00:32:46,540
Well…

640
00:32:49,060 --> 00:32:50,770
Have you ever had a lover?

641
00:32:51,060 --> 00:32:52,470
No, I haven’t.

642
00:32:53,730 --> 00:32:54,730
Then…

643
00:32:55,970 --> 00:32:57,310
Do you want one?

644
00:32:59,780 --> 00:33:01,440
How about we try being a couple?

645
00:33:02,010 --> 00:33:03,060
But...

646
00:33:04,770 --> 00:33:05,810
If we don’t click,

647
00:33:07,430 --> 00:33:09,620
I’ll step back.

648
00:33:11,910 --> 00:33:12,860
Okay.

649
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:15,060
I like a little excitement.

650
00:33:16,090 --> 00:33:17,170
Then…

651
00:33:19,710 --> 00:33:20,900
Close your eyes.

652
00:33:35,090 --> 00:33:36,100
You said...

653
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:39,300
you like excitement, right?

654
00:33:58,230 --> 00:33:59,430
It looks good on you.

655
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:04,700
Where do I tie this?

656
00:34:08,250 --> 00:34:09,389
Let me do it for you.

657
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:41,219
There.

658
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:42,610
It’s done.

659
00:34:43,510 --> 00:34:44,260
You look great.

660
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:51,909
Next mission, let’s take some photos.

661
00:34:54,690 --> 00:34:55,409
Where?

662
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,320
I bet you’ve never been here.

663
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:01,410
Our photos will appear on the LED screen.

664
00:35:02,420 --> 00:35:03,050
Sounds good?

665
00:35:03,370 --> 00:35:04,100
Really?

666
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:04,790
Shall we?

667
00:35:09,850 --> 00:35:11,620
How did you know about this place?

668
00:35:11,770 --> 00:35:14,460
It’s famous.

669
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:16,450
They just opened in Siam.

670
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:19,450
I read the reviews.

671
00:35:19,450 --> 00:35:22,030
You can play games, watch movies, and watch cartoons here.

672
00:35:22,030 --> 00:35:23,270
It has everything.

673
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:26,860
Actually, I wanted to come here for a long time,

674
00:35:27,250 --> 00:35:29,640
but my old group members all left.

675
00:35:30,250 --> 00:35:32,020
So, you’re the first person

676
00:35:32,020 --> 00:35:33,400
who made my dream come true.

677
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:35,800
When you act like a child,

678
00:35:36,290 --> 00:35:37,290
you’re quite cute,

679
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,700
Leader.

680
00:35:40,030 --> 00:35:40,780
Silly you.

681
00:35:46,070 --> 00:35:47,740
Let’s take photos here, Mai.

682
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:49,190
Sure.

683
00:35:51,690 --> 00:35:52,570
Which kind of photo?

684
00:35:53,510 --> 00:35:54,340
You choose.

685
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:59,390
This one is cute.

686
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:00,600
-How about this?
-It looks nice.

687
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,450
Sure.

688
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:04,350
How should we pose?

689
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:07,240
Let’s stand next to each other first.

690
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:07,860
Sure.

691
00:36:13,250 --> 00:36:14,820
I think we’re too far apart.

692
00:36:14,820 --> 00:36:16,140
Come a little closer.

693
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:18,430
That’s better.

694
00:36:18,770 --> 00:36:19,460
Ready?

695
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:24,780
Mhm.

696
00:36:25,470 --> 00:36:26,380
It's not good.

697
00:36:26,890 --> 00:36:29,390
You’re almost out of frame, see?

698
00:36:29,390 --> 00:36:30,850
Can you crouch down?

699
00:36:30,850 --> 00:36:31,980
Okay, you’re right.

700
00:36:31,980 --> 00:36:32,970
Here we go.

701
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:39,910
Can we move closer?

702
00:36:40,500 --> 00:36:41,190
Sure.

703
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:43,440
Where should I stand? Here?

704
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:45,570
Yes, move forward and crouch down.

705
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:04,930
While we wait for the photo,

706
00:37:04,930 --> 00:37:06,840
shall we wait in the room next door?

707
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:08,520
Sure.

708
00:37:19,010 --> 00:37:20,820
What are we doing in the recording room?

709
00:37:21,190 --> 00:37:21,840
Oh.

710
00:37:23,510 --> 00:37:24,710
Didn’t you said

711
00:37:25,450 --> 00:37:27,690
you like things that are exciting?

712
00:37:28,970 --> 00:37:30,610
But there are security cameras here.

713
00:37:36,710 --> 00:37:37,760
I already checked.

714
00:37:38,870 --> 00:37:40,200
All of them are broken.

715
00:37:46,470 --> 00:37:48,790
Is it as good as when you do CPR?

716
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,070
We removed some clothes for CPR, though.

717
00:39:01,830 --> 00:39:03,930
This room is nice. It even has an octopus.

718
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:05,830
I feel like I’m a kid again.

719
00:39:06,690 --> 00:39:08,000
You’re not that old yet.

720
00:39:09,610 --> 00:39:12,580
Even when we get old, everyone still has a little childish side.

721
00:39:15,380 --> 00:39:17,130
It feels nostalgic.

722
00:39:20,370 --> 00:39:21,360
Mai, should we...

723
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,850
bring the others here to help write our songs?

724
00:39:25,350 --> 00:39:26,660
Maybe we’ll get new ideas.

725
00:39:27,430 --> 00:39:28,760
Is bitter melon not enough?

726
00:39:29,340 --> 00:39:30,410
Now you want an octopus?

727
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:33,200
Mai.

728
00:39:34,620 --> 00:39:38,380
Thank you for helping me talk about my position yesterday.

729
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:43,820
Honestly, I still don’t know what I’m good at.

730
00:39:44,970 --> 00:39:46,730
So when Cutter asked me,

731
00:39:47,430 --> 00:39:48,610
I didn’t know how to answer.

732
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:54,030
I think I’m a jack of all trades, master of none like they say.

733
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:56,240
Who said that?

734
00:39:56,980 --> 00:39:58,150
The comment.

735
00:39:58,740 --> 00:40:00,880
Someone commented about me.

736
00:40:01,890 --> 00:40:02,850
How many people?

737
00:40:03,080 --> 00:40:03,910
One.

738
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:06,800
Just one?

739
00:40:13,710 --> 00:40:16,430
Can I be that one person instead?

740
00:40:20,810 --> 00:40:23,280
Out photos are about to go on the LED screen.

741
00:40:23,790 --> 00:40:24,900
Let’s go see it.

742
00:40:25,540 --> 00:40:26,570
Let’s go.

743
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:06,050
You want me to go undercover?

744
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:09,030
Isn’t it too difficult?

745
00:41:09,380 --> 00:41:13,340
What if I accidentally give myself away?

746
00:41:13,790 --> 00:41:14,520
Bruh.

747
00:41:14,860 --> 00:41:17,150
Even scammers have to pay you respect.

748
00:41:17,150 --> 00:41:21,240
I bet you’ll be super convincing,

749
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:22,900
except for one thing.

750
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:23,630
What?

751
00:41:24,170 --> 00:41:25,980
Your face, haha.

752
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:29,010
You keep roasting me. Are you done yet?

753
00:41:29,530 --> 00:41:32,690
Save your mouth for barking at your roommate.

754
00:41:34,550 --> 00:41:37,070
What if they catch me, Bai Liu?

755
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:39,450
There’s no way.

756
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:41,570
I know my people well.

757
00:41:41,570 --> 00:41:44,340
Just don’t blow your cover.

758
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:46,520
And I just heard that

759
00:41:46,520 --> 00:41:48,800
he fired an employee who’s a fan of our artist.

760
00:41:49,370 --> 00:41:51,000
He hasn't changed at all.

761
00:41:51,430 --> 00:41:53,060
So what do you want me to do?

762
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:57,110
I want you to apply for a job there.

763
00:41:57,570 --> 00:41:58,830
Tomorrow morning.

764
00:41:59,120 --> 00:41:59,880
Okay?

765
00:42:02,410 --> 00:42:05,460
I think Young Master has something up his sleeve.

766
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:07,110
He looks so evil.

767
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:08,220
Right?

768
00:42:09,340 --> 00:42:11,460
Okay, Bai Liu.

769
00:42:18,990 --> 00:42:21,980
(Watch the uncut version only on iQIYI and IQ.com.)

770
00:42:56,510 --> 00:42:58,670
That’s amazing. You all did a great job!

771
00:42:58,670 --> 00:43:00,480
Get ready for a poster photoshoot.

772
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,290
Who is she?

773
00:43:02,290 --> 00:43:05,450
Her name is Medyer, your new manager.

774
00:43:05,450 --> 00:43:06,710
You couldn’t afford it?

775
00:43:07,980 --> 00:43:11,070
Then I’ll take this one and this one. All of them!

776
00:43:11,070 --> 00:43:12,150
Wanna take a photo together?

777
00:43:12,150 --> 00:43:14,880
I won’t give in to anyone else but you.

778
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,350
You look so cute when you smile.

779
00:43:17,350 --> 00:43:18,300
Smile a little more.

780
00:43:18,300 --> 00:43:20,240
My smile is already right in front of me.

